Primary analyses · Hypertension
==============================================================================
  Analytic cohort: n = 2,274, incident cases = 270 (11.9%)

--- Between-person analyses ---
  (no multiple-comparison correction across the three rhythm parameters)
  Typical-day mesor         OR = 1.53, 95% CI [1.33, 1.77], p = 5.31e-09
  Typical-day amplitude     OR = 0.82, 95% CI [0.72, 0.94], p = 0.00391
  Typical-day acrophase     OR = 1.19, 95% CI [1.04, 1.36], p = 0.0103

--- Within-person analyses ---
  SD daily mesor            n = 2042  cases = 221  univariate OR = 1.20, 95% CI [1.04, 1.38], p = 0.0128
  SD daily mesor            joint with mesor: feature OR = 1.24 [1.08, 1.43], p = 0.00224; mesor OR = 1.54, p = 8.63e-08
  SD daily amplitude        n = 2042  cases = 221  univariate OR = 0.99, 95% CI [0.87, 1.13], p = 0.92
  SD daily amplitude        joint with mesor: feature OR = 1.09 [0.96, 1.25], p = 0.196; mesor OR = 1.53, p = 2.76e-07
  SD daily acrophase        n = 2042  cases = 221  univariate OR = 1.26, 95% CI [1.11, 1.43], p = 0.000295
  SD daily acrophase        joint with mesor: feature OR = 1.27 [1.11, 1.45], p = 0.000474; mesor OR = 1.50, p = 3.59e-07

